\f0\b\fs64 \cf2 Genesis 
\b0\fs24 \cf3 \

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 1
\b0\fs26 \cf3 In the beginning God created the heavens and the earth.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 The earth was without form, and void; and darkness was on the face of the deep. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 And the Spirit of God was hovering over the face of the waters. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let there be light"; and there was light. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And God saw the light, that it was good; and God divided the light from the darkness. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 God called the light Day, and the darkness He called Night. So the evening and the morning were the first day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let there be a firmament in the midst of the waters, and let it divide the waters from the waters." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Thus God made the firmament, and divided the waters which were under the firmament from the waters which were above the firmament; and it was so. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And God called the firmament Heaven. So the evening and the morning were the second day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let the waters under the heavens be gathered together into one place, and let the dry land appear"; and it was so. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And God called the dry land Earth, and the gathering together of the waters He called Seas. And God saw that it was good. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let the earth bring forth grass, the herb that yields seed, and the fruit tree that yields fruit according to its kind, whose seed is in itself, on the earth"; and it was so. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the earth brought forth grass, the herb that yields seed according to its kind, and the tree that yields fruit, whose seed is in itself according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the evening and the morning were the third day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let there be lights in the firmament of the heavens to divide the day from the night; and let them be for signs and seasons, and for days and years; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and let them be for lights in the firmament of the heavens to give light on the earth"; and it was so. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God made two great lights: the greater light to rule the day, and the lesser light to rule the night. He made the stars also. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 God set them in the firmament of the heavens to give light on the earth,\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and to rule over the day and over the night, and to divide the light from the 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 darkness. And God saw that it was good.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the evening and the morning were the fourth day. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let the waters abound with an abundance of living creatures, and let birds fly above the earth across the face of the firmament of the heavens." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So God created great sea creatures and every living thing that moves, with which the waters abounded, according to their kind, and every winged bird according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And God blessed them, saying, "Be fruitful and multiply, and fill the waters in the seas, and let birds multiply on the earth." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the evening and the morning were the fifth day. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let the earth bring forth the living creature according to its kind: cattle and creeping thing and beast of the earth, each according to its kind"; and it was so. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And God made the beast of the earth according to its kind, cattle according to its kind, and everything that creeps on the earth according to its kind. And God saw that it was good. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God said, "Let Us make man in Our image, according to Our likeness; let them have dominion over the fish of the sea, over the birds of the air, and over the cattle, over all the earth and over every creeping thing that creeps on the earth." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 27
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So God created man in His own image; in the image of God He created him; male and female He created them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 28
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God blessed them, and God said to them, "Be fruitful and multiply; fill the earth and subdue it; have dominion over the fish of the sea, over the birds of the air, and over every living thing that moves on the earth." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 29
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And God said, "See, I have given you every herb that yields seed which is on the face of all the earth, and every tree whose fruit yields seed; to you it shall be for food. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 30
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Also, to every beast of the earth, to every bird of the air, and to everything that creeps on the earth, in which there is life, I have given every green herb for food"; and it was so. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 31
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God saw everything that He had made, and indeed it was very good. So the evening and the morning were the sixth day. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 2
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Thus the heavens and the earth, and all the host of them, were finished.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And on the seventh day God ended His work which He had done, and He rested on 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 the seventh day from all His work which He had done. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then God blessed the seventh day and sanctified it, because in it He rested from all His work which God had created and made. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 This is the history of the heavens and the earth when they were created, in the day that the LORD God made the earth and the heavens, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 before any plant of the field was in the earth and before any herb of the field had grown. For the LORD God had not caused it to rain on the earth, and there was no man to till the ground; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 but a mist went up from the earth and watered the whole face of the ground.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD God formed man of the dust of the ground, and breathed into his 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 nostrils the breath of life; and man became a living being. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 The LORD God planted a garden eastward in Eden, and there He put the man whom He had formed. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And out of the ground the LORD God made every tree grow that is pleasant to the sight and good for food. The tree of life was also in the midst of the garden, and the tree of the knowledge of good and evil. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now a river went out of Eden to water the garden, and from there it parted and became four riverheads. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 The name of the first is Pishon; it is the one which skirts the whole land of Havilah, where there is gold. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the gold of that land is good. Bdellium and the onyx stone are there.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 The name of the second river is Gihon; it is the one which goes around the whole 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 land of Cush. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 The name of the third river is Hiddekel; it is the one which goes toward the east of Assyria. The fourth river is the Euphrates. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the LORD God took the man and put him in the garden of Eden to tend and keep it. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD God commanded the man, saying, "Of every tree of the garden you may freely eat; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 but of the tree of the knowledge of good and evil you shall not eat, for in the day that you eat of it you shall surely die." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD God said, "It is not good that man should be alone; I will make him a helper comparable to him." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Out of the ground the LORD God formed every beast of the field and every bird of the air, and brought them to Adam to see what he would call them. And whatever Adam called each living creature, that was its name. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Adam gave names to all cattle, to the birds of the air, and to every beast of the field. But for Adam there was not found a helper comparable to him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD God caused a deep sleep to fall on Adam, and he slept; and He took one of his ribs, and closed up the flesh in its place. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the rib which the LORD God had taken from man He made into a woman, and He brought her to the man. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Adam said: "This is now bone of my bones And flesh of my flesh; She shall be called Woman, Because she was taken out of Man." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Therefore a man shall leave his father and mother and be joined to his wife, and they shall become one flesh. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And they were both naked, the man and his wife, and were not ashamed.\uc0\u8232 
\b\fs64 \cf4 3
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Now the serpent was more cunning than any beast of the field which the LORD 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 God had made. And he said to the woman, "Has God indeed said, "You shall not eat of every tree of the garden'?" 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the woman said to the serpent, "We may eat the fruit of the trees of the garden; 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 but of the fruit of the tree which is in the midst of the garden, God has said, "You 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 shall not eat it, nor shall you touch it, lest you die."'\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the serpent said to the woman, "You will not surely die. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 For God knows that in the day you eat of it your eyes will be opened, and you will be like God, knowing good and evil." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So when the woman saw that the tree was good for food, that it was pleasant to the eyes, and a tree desirable to make one wise, she took of its fruit and ate. She also gave to her husband with her, and he ate. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the eyes of both of them were opened, and they knew that they were naked; and they sewed fig leaves together and made themselves coverings. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And they heard the sound of the LORD God walking in the garden in the cool of the day, and Adam and his wife hid themselves from the presence of the LORD God among the trees of the garden. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the LORD God called to Adam and said to him, "Where are you?"\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So he said, "I heard Your voice in the garden, and I was afraid because I was 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 naked; and I hid myself." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And He said, "Who told you that you were naked? Have you eaten from the tree of which I commanded you that you should not eat?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the man said, "The woman whom You gave to be with me, she gave me of the tree, and I ate." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD God said to the woman, "What is this you have done?" The woman said, "The serpent deceived me, and I ate." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the LORD God said to the serpent: "Because you have done this, You are cursed more than all cattle, And more than every beast of the field; On your belly you shall go, And you shall eat dust All the days of your life. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And I will put enmity Between you and the woman, And between your seed and her Seed; He shall bruise your head, And you shall bruise His heel." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 To the woman He said: "I will greatly multiply your sorrow and your conception; In pain you shall bring forth children; Your desire shall be for your husband, And he shall rule over you." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then to Adam He said, "Because you have heeded the voice of your wife, and have eaten from the tree of which I commanded you, saying, "You shall not eat of it': "Cursed is the ground for your sake; In toil you shall eat of it All the days of your life. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Both thorns and thistles it shall bring forth for you, And you shall eat the herb of the field. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 In the sweat of your face you shall eat bread Till you return to the ground, For out of it you were taken; For dust you are, And to dust you shall return." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Adam called his wife's name Eve, because she was the mother of all living. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Also for Adam and his wife the LORD God made tunics of skin, and clothed them. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the LORD God said, "Behold, the man has become like one of Us, to know good and evil. And now, lest he put out his hand and take also of the tree of life, and eat, and live forever"-- 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 therefore the LORD God sent him out of the garden of Eden to till the ground from which he was taken. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So He drove out the man; and He placed cherubim at the east of the garden of Eden, and a flaming sword which turned every way, to guard the way to the tree of life. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 4
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Now Adam knew Eve his wife, and she conceived and bore Cain, and said, "I have acquired a man from the LORD." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then she bore again, this time his brother Abel. Now Abel was a keeper of sheep, but Cain was a tiller of the ground. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And in the process of time it came to pass that Cain brought an offering of the fruit of the ground to the LORD. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Abel also brought of the firstborn of his flock and of their fat. And the LORD respected Abel and his offering, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 but He did not respect Cain and his offering. And Cain was very angry, and his countenance fell. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So the LORD said to Cain, "Why are you angry? And why has your countenance fallen? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 If you do well, will you not be accepted? And if you do not do well, sin lies at the door. And its desire is for you, but you should rule over it." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now Cain talked with Abel his brother; and it came to pass, when they were in the field, that Cain rose up against Abel his brother and killed him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then the LORD said to Cain, "Where is Abel your brother?" He said, "I do not know. Am I my brother's keeper?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And He said, "What have you done? The voice of your brother's blood cries out to Me from the ground. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So now you are cursed from the earth, which has opened its mouth to receive your brother's blood from your hand. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 When you till the ground, it shall no longer yield its strength to you. A fugitive and a vagabond you shall be on the earth." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Cain said to the LORD, "My punishment is greater than I can bear! 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Surely You have driven me out this day from the face of the ground; I shall be hidden from Your face; I shall be a fugitive and a vagabond on the earth, and it will happen that anyone who finds me will kill me." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the LORD said to him, "Therefore, whoever kills Cain, vengeance shall be taken on him sevenfold." And the LORD set a mark on Cain, lest anyone finding him should kill him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Cain went out from the presence of the LORD and dwelt in the land of Nod on the east of Eden. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Cain knew his wife, and she conceived and bore Enoch. And he built a city, and called the name of the city after the name of his son--Enoch. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 To Enoch was born Irad; and Irad begot Mehujael, and Mehujael begot Methushael, and Methushael begot Lamech. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Lamech took for himself two wives: the name of one was Adah, and the name of the second was Zillah. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Adah bore Jabal. He was the father of those who dwell in tents and have livestock. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 His brother's name was Jubal. He was the father of all those who play the harp and flute. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And as for Zillah, she also bore Tubal-Cain, an instructor of every craftsman in bronze and iron. And the sister of Tubal-Cain was Naamah. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Lamech said to his wives: "Adah and Zillah, hear my voice; Wives of Lamech, listen to my speech! For I have killed a man for wounding me, Even a young man for hurting me. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 If Cain shall be avenged sevenfold, Then Lamech seventy-sevenfold."\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Adam knew his wife again, and she bore a son and named him Seth, "For God 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 has appointed another seed for me instead of Abel, whom Cain killed." 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And as for Seth, to him also a son was born; and he named him Enosh. Then men began to call on the name of the LORD. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 5
\b0\fs26 \cf3 This is the book of the genealogy of Adam. In the day that God created man, He made him in the likeness of God. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 He created them male and female, and blessed them and called them Mankind in the day they were created. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Adam lived one hundred and thirty years, and begot a son in his own likeness, after his image, and named him Seth. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 After he begot Seth, the days of Adam were eight hundred years; and he had sons and daughters. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So all the days that Adam lived were nine hundred and thirty years; and he died. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Seth lived one hundred and five years, and begot Enosh. 
