\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Esau took his wives from the daughters of Canaan: Adah the daughter of Elon the Hittite; Aholibamah the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon the Hivite; 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 and Basemath, Ishmael's daughter, sister of Nebajoth. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now Adah bore Eliphaz to Esau, and Basemath bore Reuel. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Aholibamah bore Jeush, Jaalam, and Korah. These were the sons of Esau who were born to him in the land of Canaan. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Esau took his wives, his sons, his daughters, and all the persons of his household, his cattle and all his animals, and all his goods which he had gained in the land of Canaan, and went to a country away from the presence of his brother Jacob. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 For their possessions were too great for them to dwell together, and the land where they were strangers could not support them because of their livestock. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Esau dwelt in Mount Seir. Esau is Edom.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And this is the genealogy of Esau the father of the Edomites in Mount Seir. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the names of Esau's sons: Eliphaz the son of Adah the wife of Esau, and Reuel the son of Basemath the wife of Esau. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the sons of Eliphaz were Teman, Omar, Zepho, Gatam, and Kenaz. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now Timna was the concubine of Eliphaz, Esau's son, and she bore Amalek to Eliphaz. These were the sons of Adah, Esau's wife. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Reuel: Nahath, Zerah, Shammah, and Mizzah. These were the sons of Basemath, Esau's wife. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Aholibamah, Esau's wife, the daughter of Anah, the daughter of Zibeon. And she bore to Esau: Jeush, Jaalam, and Korah. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the chiefs of the sons of Esau. The sons of Eliphaz, the firstborn son of Esau, were Chief Teman, Chief Omar, Chief Zepho, Chief Kenaz, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Chief Korah, Chief Gatam, and Chief Amalek. These were the chiefs of Eliphaz in the land of Edom. They were the sons of Adah. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Reuel, Esau's son: Chief Nahath, Chief Zerah, Chief Shammah, and Chief Mizzah. These were the chiefs of Reuel in the land of Edom. These were the sons of Basemath, Esau's wife. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And these were the sons of Aholibamah, Esau's wife: Chief Jeush, Chief Jaalam, and Chief Korah. These were the chiefs who descended from Aholibamah, Esau's wife, the daughter of Anah. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Esau, who is Edom, and these were their chiefs.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Seir the Horite who inhabited the land: Lotan, Shobal, 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 Zibeon, Anah, 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Dishon, Ezer, and Dishan. These were the chiefs of the Horites, the sons of Seir, in the land of Edom. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the sons of Lotan were Hori and Hemam. Lotan's sister was Timna. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Shobal: Alvan, Manahath, Ebal, Shepho, and Onam. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Zibeon: both Ajah and Anah. This was the Anah who found the water in the wilderness as he pastured the donkeys of his father Zibeon. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the children of Anah: Dishon and Aholibamah the daughter of Anah. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Dishon: Hemdan, Eshban, Ithran, and Cheran.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 27
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Ezer: Bilhan, Zaavan, and Akan.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 28
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the sons of Dishan: Uz and Aran. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 29
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 These were the chiefs of the Horites: Chief Lotan, Chief Shobal, Chief Zibeon, Chief Anah, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 30
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Chief Dishon, Chief Ezer, and Chief Dishan. These were the chiefs of the Horites, according to their chiefs in the land of Seir. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 31
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now these were the kings who reigned in the land of Edom before any king reigned over the children of Israel: 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 32
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Bela the son of Beor reigned in Edom, and the name of his city was Dinhabah. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 33
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And when Bela died, Jobab the son of Zerah of Bozrah reigned in his place. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 34
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 When Jobab died, Husham of the land of the Temanites reigned in his place. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 35
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And when Husham died, Hadad the son of Bedad, who attacked Midian in the field of Moab, reigned in his place. And the name of his city was Avith. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 36
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 When Hadad died, Samlah of Masrekah reigned in his place.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 37
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And when Samlah died, Saul of Rehoboth-by-the-River reigned in his place. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 38
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 When Saul died, Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor reigned in his place. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 39
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And when Baal-Hanan the son of Achbor died, Hadar reigned in his place; and the name of his city was Pau. His wife's name was Mehetabel, the daughter of Matred, the daughter of Mezahab. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 40
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And these were the names of the chiefs of Esau, according to their families and their places, by their names: Chief Timnah, Chief Alvah, Chief Jetheth, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 41
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Chief Aholibamah, Chief Elah, Chief Pinon, 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 42
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Chief Kenaz, Chief Teman, Chief Mibzar, 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 43
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Chief Magdiel, and Chief Iram. These were the chiefs of Edom, according to their dwelling places in the land of their possession. Esau was the father of the Edomites. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 37
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Now Jacob dwelt in the land where his father was a stranger, in the land of Canaan. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 This is the history of Jacob. Joseph, being seventeen years old, was feeding the flock with his brothers. And the lad was with the sons of Bilhah and the sons of Zilpah, his father's wives; and Joseph brought a bad report of them to his father. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now Israel loved Joseph more than all his children, because he was the son of his old age. Also he made him a tunic of many colors. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 But when his brothers saw that their father loved him more than all his brothers, they hated him and could not speak peaceably to him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now Joseph had a dream, and he told it to his brothers; and they hated him even more. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So he said to them, "Please hear this dream which I have dreamed: 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 There we were, binding sheaves in the field. Then behold, my sheaf arose and also stood upright; and indeed your sheaves stood all around and bowed down to my sheaf." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And his brothers said to him, "Shall you indeed reign over us? Or shall you indeed have dominion over us?" So they hated him even more for his dreams and for his words. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then he dreamed still another dream and told it to his brothers, and said, "Look, I have dreamed another dream. And this time, the sun, the moon, and the eleven stars bowed down to me." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So he told it to his father and his brothers; and his father rebuked him and said to him, "What is this dream that you have dreamed? Shall your mother and I and your brothers indeed come to bow down to the earth before you?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And his brothers envied him, but his father kept the matter in mind. 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then his brothers went to feed their father's flock in Shechem. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Israel said to Joseph, "Are not your brothers feeding the flock in Shechem? Come, I will send you to them." So he said to him, "Here I am." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then he said to him, "Please go and see if it is well with your brothers and well with the flocks, and bring back word to me." So he sent him out of the Valley of Hebron, and he went to Shechem. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now a certain man found him, and there he was, wandering in the field. And the man asked him, saying, "What are you seeking?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So he said, "I am seeking my brothers. Please tell me where they are feeding their flocks." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the man said, "They have departed from here, for I heard them say, "Let us go to Dothan."' So Joseph went after his brothers and found them in Dothan. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now when they saw him afar off, even before he came near them, they conspired against him to kill him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then they said to one another, "Look, this dreamer is coming!\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Come therefore, let us now kill him and cast him into some pit; and we shall say, 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 "Some wild beast has devoured him.' We shall see what will become of his dreams!" 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 But Reuben heard it, and he delivered him out of their hands, and said, "Let us not kill him." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Reuben said to them, "Shed no blood, but cast him into this pit which is in the wilderness, and do not lay a hand on him"--that he might deliver him out of their hands, and bring him back to his father. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So it came to pass, when Joseph had come to his brothers, that they stripped Joseph of his tunic, the tunic of many colors that was on him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then they took him and cast him into a pit. And the pit was empty; there was no water in it. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And they sat down to eat a meal. Then they lifted their eyes and looked, and there was a company of Ishmaelites, coming from Gilead with their camels, bearing spices, balm, and myrrh, on their way to carry them down to Egypt. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Judah said to his brothers, "What profit is there if we kill our brother and conceal his blood? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 27
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Come and let us sell him to the Ishmaelites, and let not our hand be upon him, for he is our brother and our flesh." And his brothers listened. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 28
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Midianite traders passed by; so the brothers pulled Joseph up and lifted him out of the pit, and sold him to the Ishmaelites for twenty shekels of silver. And they took Joseph to Egypt. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 29
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Reuben returned to the pit, and indeed Joseph was not in the pit; and he tore his clothes. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 30
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And he returned to his brothers and said, "The lad is no more; and I, where shall I go?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 31
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So they took Joseph's tunic, killed a kid of the goats, and dipped the tunic in the blood. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 32
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then they sent the tunic of many colors, and they brought it to their father and said, "We have found this. Do you know whether it is your son's tunic or not?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 33
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And he recognized it and said, "It is my son's tunic. A wild beast has devoured him. Without doubt Joseph is torn to pieces." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 34
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Jacob tore his clothes, put sackcloth on his waist, and mourned for his son many days. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 35
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And all his sons and all his daughters arose to comfort him; but he refused to be comforted, and he said, "For I shall go down into the grave to my son in mourning." Thus his father wept for him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 36
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now the Midianites had sold him in Egypt to Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh and captain of the guard. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 38
\b0\fs26 \cf3 It came to pass at that time that Judah departed from his brothers, and visited a certain Adullamite whose name was Hirah. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Judah saw there a daughter of a certain Canaanite whose name was Shua, and he married her and went in to her. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So she conceived and bore a son, and he called his name Er.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 She conceived again and bore a son, and she called his name Onan. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And she conceived yet again and bore a son, and called his name Shelah. He was at Chezib when she bore him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Judah took a wife for Er his firstborn, and her name was Tamar.\uc0\u8232 
\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 But Er, Judah's firstborn, was wicked in the sight of the LORD, and the LORD killed 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 him. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Judah said to Onan, "Go in to your brother's wife and marry her, and raise up an heir to your brother." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 But Onan knew that the heir would not be his; and it came to pass, when he went in to his brother's wife, that he emitted on the ground, lest he should give an heir to his brother. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 10
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And the thing which he did displeased the LORD; therefore He killed him also. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 11
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Judah said to Tamar his daughter-in-law, "Remain a widow in your father's house till my son Shelah is grown." For he said, "Lest he also die like his brothers." And Tamar went and dwelt in her father's house. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 12
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now in the process of time the daughter of Shua, Judah's wife, died; and Judah was comforted, and went up to his sheepshearers at Timnah, he and his friend Hirah the Adullamite. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 13
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it was told Tamar, saying, "Look, your father-in-law is going up to Timnah to shear his sheep." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 14
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So she took off her widow's garments, covered herself with a veil and wrapped herself, and sat in an open place which was on the way to Timnah; for she saw that Shelah was grown, and she was not given to him as a wife. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 15
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 When Judah saw her, he thought she was a harlot, because she had covered her face. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 16
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then he turned to her by the way, and said, "Please let me come in to you"; for he did not know that she was his daughter-in-law. So she said, "What will you give me, that you may come in to me?" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 17
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And he said, "I will send a young goat from the flock." So she said, "Will you give me a pledge till you send it? 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 18
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then he said, "What pledge shall I give you?" So she said, "Your signet and cord, and your staff that is in your hand." Then he gave them to her, and went in to her, and she conceived by him. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 19
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So she arose and went away, and laid aside her veil and put on the garments of her widowhood. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 20
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And Judah sent the young goat by the hand of his friend the Adullamite, to receive his pledge from the woman's hand, but he did not find her. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 21
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then he asked the men of that place, saying, "Where is the harlot who was openly by the roadside?" And they said, "There was no harlot in this place." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 22
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So he returned to Judah and said, "I cannot find her. Also, the men of the place said there was no harlot in this place." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 23
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then Judah said, "Let her take them for herself, lest we be shamed; for I sent this young goat and you have not found her." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 24
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it came to pass, about three months after, that Judah was told, saying, "Tamar your daughter-in-law has played the harlot; furthermore she is with child by harlotry." So Judah said, "Bring her out and let her be burned!" 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 25
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 When she was brought out, she sent to her father-in-law, saying, "By the man to whom these belong, I am with child." And she said, "Please determine whose these are--the signet and cord, and staff." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 26
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Judah acknowledged them and said, "She has been more righteous than I, because I did not give her to Shelah my son." And he never knew her again. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 27
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Now it came to pass, at the time for giving birth, that behold, twins were in her womb. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 28
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And so it was, when she was giving birth, that the one put out his hand; and the midwife took a scarlet thread and bound it on his hand, saying, "This one came out first." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 29
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Then it happened, as he drew back his hand, that his brother came out unexpectedly; and she said, "How did you break through? This breach be upon you!" Therefore his name was called Perez. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 30
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Afterward his brother came out who had the scarlet thread on his hand. And his name was called Zerah. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl740\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b\fs64 \cf4 39
\b0\fs26 \cf3 Now Joseph had been taken down to Egypt. And Potiphar, an officer of Pharaoh, captain of the guard, an Egyptian, bought him from the Ishmaelites who 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl300\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs26 \cf3 had taken him down there. 
\f0\fs24 \
\pard\pardeftab720\sl180\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 2
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 The LORD was with Joseph, and he was a successful man; and he was in the house of his master the Egyptian. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 3
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And his master saw that the LORD was with him and that the LORD made all he did to prosper in his hand. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 4
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So Joseph found favor in his sight, and served him. Then he made him overseer of his house, and all that he had he put under his authority. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 5
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 So it was, from the time that he had made him overseer of his house and all that he had, that the LORD blessed the Egyptian's house for Joseph's sake; and the blessing of the LORD was on all that he had in the house and in the field. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 6
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 Thus he left all that he had in Joseph's hand, and he did not know what he had except for the bread which he ate. Now Joseph was handsome in form and appearance. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 7
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 And it came to pass after these things that his master's wife cast longing eyes on Joseph, and she said, "Lie with me." 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 8
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 But he refused and said to his master's wife, "Look, my master does not know what is with me in the house, and he has committed all that he has to my hand. 
\f0\fs24 \

\f1\fs16 \cf2 \up13 9
\fs26 \cf3 \up0 There is no one greater in this house than I, nor has he kept back anything from me but you, because you are his wife. How then can I do this great wickedness, and sin against God?" 
